{"title_page": "List of countries by median age", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n[[Image:Median age by country, 2016.svg|thumb|550px|Median age by country, CIA World Factbook 2018 est.]]\n\nThis article is a '''list of countries by [[median]] age'''.\n\n== Methodology ==\nMedian age is the age that divides a population into two numerically equally sized groups - that is, half the people are younger than this age and half are older. It is a single index that summarizes the age distribution of a population.<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/fields/2177.html Field Listing - Median age], [[The World Factbook]], [[Central Intelligence Agency]]. Data last updated on April 2, 2009.</ref>\n\nCurrently, the median age ranges from a low of about 15 in [[Demographics of Niger|Niger]] to 40 or more in several [[Europe]]an countries, [[Demographics of Canada|Canada]], and [[Demographics of Japan|Japan]].<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/docs/notesanddefs.html#2177]</ref> The median age for women tends to be much greater than that of men in some of the [[ex-Soviet republics]], while in the [[Global South]] the difference is far smaller or is reversed.\n\n== Countries ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: right\"\n|+ CIA World Factbook 2018 est.<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/resources/the-world-factbook/fields/343rank.html CIA The World Factbook/ Median Age 2018]. Retrieved 03/12/2017.</ref>\n|-\n! Country/Territory !! Rank !! Median<br/>(Years) !! Male<br/>(Years) !! Female <br/>(Years)\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Afghanistan}} || 208 || 18.9 || 18.8 || 18.9\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Albania}} || 95 || 32.9 || 31.6 || 34.3\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Algeria}} || 136 || 28.1 || 27.8 || 28.4\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | ''{{flagcountry|American Samoa}}'' || 122 || 25.5 || 25.1 || 26.0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Andorra}}