 ranges from a low of about 15 in [[Demographics of Niger|Niger]] to 40 or more in several [[Europe]]an countries, [[Demographics of Canada|Canada]] and [[Demographics of Japan|Japan]].<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/docs/notesanddefs.html#2177]</ref> The median age for women tends to be much greater than that of men in some of the [[ex-Soviet republics]], while in the [[Global South]] the difference is far smaller or is reversed.\n\n== Countries ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: right\"\n|+ CIA World Factbook 2018 est.<ref>[https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/resources/the-world-factbook/fields/343rank.html CIA The World Factbook/ Median Age 2018]. Retrieved 03/12/2017.</ref>\n|-\n! Country/Territory !! Rank !! Median<br/>(Years) !! Male<br/>(Years) !! Female <br/>(Years)\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Afghanistan}} || 208 || 18.9 || 18.8 || 18.9\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Albania}} || 95 || 32.9 || 31.6 || 34.3\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Algeria}} || 136 || 28.1 || 27.8 || 28.4\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | ''{{flagcountry|American Samoa}}'' || 122 || 25.5 || 25.1 || 26.0\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Andorra}} || 10 || 44.3 || 44.4 || 44.1\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Angola}} || 214 || 15.9 || 15.4 || 16.3\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | ''{{flagcountry|Anguilla}}'' || 79 || 34.8 || 32.9|| 36.7\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Antigua and Barbuda}} || 102 || 31.9 || 30.0 || 33.5\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Argentina}} || 105 || 31.7 || 30.5 || 32.9\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Armenia}} || 80 || 35.1 || 33.3 || 36.9\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | ''{{flagcountry|Aruba}}'' || 55 || 39.3 || 37.5 || 41.1\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Australia}} || 58 || 38.7 || 37.9 || 39.5\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Austria}} || 13 || 44.0 || 42.8 || 45.1\n|-\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagcountry|Azerbaijan}} || 107 || 21.4 || 19.8 || 23.0\n|-\n| align=\"le