e|Ottoman]] era [[yal\u0131|waterfront houses (''yal\u0131'')]] on the Bosphorus.\nFile:Elbiseci Ahmet Bey Yal\u0131s\u0131 and Esre Umur Yal\u0131s\u0131 in Kanl\u0131ca on the Bosphorus, Turkey 001.jpg|[[Ottoman Empire|Ottoman]] era [[yal\u0131|waterfront houses (''yal\u0131'')]] on the Bosphorus.\nFile:Boat on Bosphorus.JPG|Boat on Bosphorus as seen from Sultanahmet street.\nFile:Istanbulbosphorusfrombridge.jpg|A view of the Bosporus strait, with the [[Fatih Sultan Mehmet Bridge]] visible in the background.\nFile:Cruise ship and Seabus in Istanbul.jpg|A [[cruise ship]] (left) and [[\u0130DO|Seabus]] (right) navigating through the Bosporus, with the [[Dolmabah\u00e7e Palace]] visible at the right end of the frame.\nFile:Istanbul Levent skyline.jpg|Skyline of [[Levent]] as seen from the [[Khedive Palace]] gardens on the Asian coast of the Bosporus. [[Istanbul Sapphire]] is the first skyscraper at right.\n</gallery>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Great Istanbul Tunnel]], a proposed three-level road-rail undersea tunnel.\n* [[List of maritime incidents in the Turkish Straits]]\n* [[Public transport in Istanbul]]\n* [[Rail transport in Turkey]]\n* [[Istanbul Canal]]\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikivoyage|Istanbul/Bosphorus}}\n{{Commons}}\n* {{Cite NSRW|wstitle=Bosphorus|short=x}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Bosphorus| ]]\n[[Category:Landforms of Istanbul Province]]\n[[Category:Straits of the Mediterranean Sea]]\n[[Category:Straits of Turkey]]\n[[Category:Tourism in Istanbul]]\n[[Category:Turkish Straits]]\n", "name_user": "Kutkut16~enwiki", "label": "safe", "comment": "\"Chryspolis\" corrected to \"Chrysopolis\"", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bosporus"}
